These men were later pardoned when they announced they had deserted from Lafitte's ship in Galveston when they discovered it did not have a valid privateering commission. (Davis (2005), p. 436).↩
Davis (2005), p. 437.↩
Davis (2005), p. 438.↩
The General Victoria was rescued after more than two weeks, and the starving crew members were given rewards for having taken it from a pirate. (Davis (2005), p. 439).↩
